A madala, believed to be 68-years-old,
was found with deadly injuries after he allegedly fell from the second floor at
a block of flats in Northdale, Pietermaritzburg on Sunday afternoon. “Shortly after 1 pm on Sunday
afternoon paramedics from ER24 arrived on the scene where they found the scene
cordoned off by local police. Upon assessment, they found an
elderly man with fatal injuries lying near the building,” ER24 spokesperson
Russel Meiring said. He said according to bystanders the
man seemingly fell from the balcony on the second floor. “There was nothing that paramedics
could do for him and he was declared dead on the scene,” he added. Local authorities on the scene will
conduct an investigation.